assertBestEver

public static void assertBestEver(EnergyProfile profile,
                                  java.lang.String identifier)
Checks whether or not a given EnergyProfile represents the best profiled energy consumption for all EnergyProfiles stored for this identifier.

Parameters:
profile - The EnergyProfiles.
identifier - Used to identify the associated EnergyProfiles for a certain assert statement. Should be unique for each assert statement to avoid side effects.

assertBestEver

public static void assertBestEver(EnergyProfile profile,
                                  java.lang.String identifier,
                                  float relativeDelta,
                                  double absoluteDelta)
Checks whether or not a given EnergyProfile represents the best profiled energy consumption for all EnergyProfiles stored for this identifier.

Parameters:
profile - The EnergyProfiles.
identifier - Used to identify the associated EnergyProfiles for a certain assert statement. Should be unique for each assert statement to avoid side effects.
relativeDelta - The maximum relative delta two profiles shall have to fulfill the assertion Given in percentage (0.0 .. 1.0). The maximum of the relative and absolute delta will be used during assertion checking.
absoluteDelta - The maximum absolute delta two profiles shall have to fulfill the assertion (given in mJ, >= 0.0). The maximum of the relative and absolute delta will be used during assertion checking.

assertDecrease

public static void assertDecrease(EnergyProfile profile,
                                  java.lang.String identifier,
                                  int numberOfRuns,
                                  float relativeDelta,
                                  double absoluteDelta)
Checks whether or not a given EnergyProfile represents a decreased energy consumption of a given percentage or absolute delta w.r.t. a given number of the last N EnergyProfiles stored for this identifier.

Parameters:
profile - The EnergyProfiles.
identifier - Used to identify the associated EnergyProfiles for a certain assert statement. Should be unique for each assert statement to avoid side effects.
numberOfRuns - The number of runs of which the given EnergyProfile should be compared.
relativeDelta - The relative delta used to check the assertion given in percentage (0.0 .. 1.0). The maximum of the relative and absolute delta will be used during assertion checking.
absoluteDelta - The absolute delta used to check the assertion (given in mJ, >= 0.0). The maximum of the relative and absolute delta will be used during assertion checking.

assertMaxWatts

public static void assertMaxWatts(EnergyProfile profile,
                                  double expectedPeak)
Compares an expected energy consumption peak in mW with the real measured values from an EnergyProfile. Please note that the peak highly depends on the refresh rate within the JouleProfiler used for the EnergyProfile's creation.

Parameters:
profile - The EnergyProfile.
expectedPeak - The expected peak in mW.

Parameters:
profiles - The EnergyProfiles.
expectedPeak - The expected peak in mW.
